chunk_content: V • If an established user has multiple follow-up visits within the same reporting period, they should E N only be counted once, in accordance with their most recent visit in the reporting period. This T applies to individuals on any PrEP method. I O o If an individual is on a long-acting injectable PrEP method in which the injection schedule N requires more than one injection administration visit in a single reporting period (e.g., CAB LA injections administered every 8 weeks and 2 injection visits fall within the same reporting period), that user can only be counted under PrEP_CT once in the given reporting period. • If an individual tests positive at his or her PrEP follow-up appointment and is then initiated on PEPFAR-supported treatment in the same reporting period, that individual could be counted as PREP_CT in addition to TX_NEW and TX_CURR (given successful transfer into the ART program) within that reporting period.
